-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP: - Canadian Pacific Railway, Encana
-- 
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 07:23AM EDT
-- None



Oct 2 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Canadian Pacific Railway and Encana, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: Raymond James raises to strong buy from outperform * Encana <ECA.TO>: Deutsche Bank raises to buy - Theflyonthewall.com  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * Bank of Nova Scotia <BNS.TO>: TD Securities cuts to hold; cuts target to C$75 from C$77 * Barrick Gold Corp <ABX.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to hold rating; price target to C$20 * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$237 from C$188;hold * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: Raymond James raises to strong buy from outperform * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: Raymond James raises target price to C$280 from C$220 * Com Dev International <CDV.TO>: Paradigm raises target price to C$6.50; rating buy * Encana <ECA.TO>: Deutsche Bank raises to buy - Theflyonthewall.com * Fortis Inc <FTS.TO>: RBC raises target price to C$37 from C$36; rating sector perform * Saputo <SAP.TO>:NBF adjusts target to C$33 from C$66 to reflect share split;sector perform * Sherritt International <S.TO>: NBF cuts target to C$5.35 from C$5.80; rating outperform * Sherritt International <S.TO>: Desjardins cuts target price to C$5.50 from C$6; rating buy * Trican Well Service Ltd <TCW.TO>: PI Financial cuts target to C$20 from C$23; rating buy * Veresen <VSN.TO>: TD Securities raises to buy from hold; ups target to C$19.50 from C$19